HEADWORD: Quintine
<hw>Quin"tine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>quintus</ets> the fifth: cf. F. <ets>quintine</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The embryonic sac of an ovule, sometimes regarded
as an innermost fifth integument. Cf. <er>Quartine</er>, and
<er>Tercine</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

